Nigerian Policeman Among 12 Dead in Reprisal Clashes in Jos, Thisday Says

-- B y   P a u l   O k o l o
-- 
2011-02-16T12:54:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/nigerian-policeman-among-12-dead-in-reprisal-clashes-in-jos-thisday-says.html
A policeman was among 12 people
killed in new fighting between Muslims and Christians in Jos,
the capital of north-central  Nigeria ’s Plateau state,  ThisDay 
newspaper reported, citing witnesses it didn’t identify.  A Muslim trader in one of the city’s markets stabbed to
death a policeman, said to be a Christian, provoking reprisal
attacks from other Christians, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  State police Commissioner Abdulrahman Akano confirmed the
death of the officer and said four people were arrested for
taking part in the clashes, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Okolo in Abuja 
 pokolo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 